Setting Up and Running Jsontron.
Please follow below steps:
1. Download and Install node.js from below location
https://nodejs.org/en/download/

2. Open a command prompt and verify that node is installed
>>  node  -version
>> npm -version


3. Install jsontron module by running below command
>> npm  i   jsontron

4. Go to node_module folder
>> cd node_modules

5. Go to jsontron lib folder
	>> cd jsontron\lib
	
6. Run the module with below command
	>> node JSONValidator -i ..\data\dissertation\pattern\loandata_pattern_good1.json -r ..\data\dissertation\pattern\loandata-rules_dissertation_pattern_good1.json


You should see something like below:
{ _: [],
  i: '..\\data\\dissertation\\pattern\\loandata_pattern_good1.json',
  r: '..\\data\\dissertation\\pattern\\loandata-rules_dissertation_pattern_good1.json' }
Parsing Pattern: precheck_pattern
Parsing Pattern: patternid1
Parsing Pattern: patternid2
Parsing Pattern: patternid3
4 Pattern(s) Requested.
4 Pattern(s) Processed.
0 Pattern(s)  Ignored.
**** THIS INSTANCE IS SEMANTICALLY VALID ****
